cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses a new mobile network architecture, C-RAN, which involves cooperative baseband processing and information sharing among multiple cells. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper formulates the utility of each user using a convex delay cost function, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The C-RAN architecture involves centralizing the baseband processing resources in a virtualized BBU pool, which can be seen as a control system. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The scheduling algorithm designed in the paper involves grouping users into small user groups and matching channels to maximize system utility, which can be seen as a distributed computing problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the adaptability of C-RAN architecture to nonuniform traffic, which is relevant to multimedia applications.
